            (collectively, the &ldquo;Service&rdquo;). By accessing or using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
            If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">2. Definitions</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
            <li><strong>&ldquo;Service&rdquo;</strong> means the OpenModeration platform, including all APIs, dashboards, documentation, and related tools.</li>
            <li><strong>&ldquo;You&rdquo;</strong> or <strong>&ldquo;User&rdquo;</strong> means the individual or entity using the Service.</li>
            <li><strong>&ldquo;Content&rdquo;</strong> means any text, data, or material submitted to the Service for moderation.</li>
            <li><strong>&ldquo;Self-Hosted&rdquo;</strong> means the open-source software deployed on your own infrastructure under AGPL v3.</li>
            <li><strong>&ldquo;Cloud Service&rdquo;</strong> means the managed SaaS offering hosted by Logora.</li>
            <li><strong>&ldquo;BYOK&rdquo;</strong> means Bring Your Own Keys: using your own provider accounts and API keys.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">3. Account Registration</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To use the Cloud Service, you must create an account with accurate and complete information.
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for all activities
            that occur under your account. You must notify us immediately of any unauthorized use.
            You must be at least 18 years old to create an account.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">4. License — Self-Hosted</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The self-hosted version of OpenModeration is licensed under the
            <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-500" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
              <strong>GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPL v3)</strong>
            </a>.
            You may use, study, modify, and distribute the software in accordance with that license.
            The AGPL v3 requires that modified versions of the software, when used to provide a service over a network,
            make the source code available to users of that service.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">5. Cloud Service</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The managed cloud service is provided on a subscription basis. Usage is subject to the rate limits,
            features, and quotas of your chosen plan as described on our
            <a href="/pricing" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-500">Pricing</a> page.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We strive for high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted access.
            We reserve the right to suspend or terminate access to the Cloud Service for accounts that violate
            these Terms or our Acceptable Use Policy, with notice where reasonably possible.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">6. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">You agree not to use OpenModeration for:</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
            <li>Any illegal activity or the facilitation of illegal content under applicable laws.</li>
            <li>Attempting to reverse-engineer, decompile, or extract provider APIs through the platform.</li>
            <li>Circumventing rate limits, authentication, or security measures.</li>
            <li>Transmitting malware, viruses, or any malicious code.</li>
            <li>Moderating content that you do not have the legal right to process.</li>
            <li>Any activity that violates the terms of service of third-party providers integrated via BYOK.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We reserve the right to investigate and take appropriate action against violations, including
            account suspension, termination, and reporting to law enforcement authorities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">7. Fees and Payment</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Free plan:</strong> The Free plan is provided at no cost for up to 1,000 moderation requests per month.
            Features may be subject to limitations as described on our Pricing page.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            <strong>Paid plans:</strong> Paid subscriptions are billed monthly or annually as selected.
            Fees are non-refundable except as required by applicable law. We may change pricing with 30 days&rsquo;
            notice for your next billing cycle. BYOK usage is not marked up; you pay your providers directly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">8. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>Our IP:</strong> OpenModeration software, documentation, website, branding, and all related
            materials are the intellectual property of Logora and are protected by copyright and other laws.
            The self-hosted software is provided under AGPL v3; the Cloud Service and proprietary components
            are not covered by the AGPL license.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            <strong>Your Content:</strong> You retain all rights to the content you submit for moderation.
            We claim no ownership over your content. You grant us a limited license to process your content
            solely for the purpose of providing the Service and as described in our
            <a href="/privacy" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-500">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">9. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            OpenModeration integrates with third-party AI providers (e.g., OpenAI, Azure, Mistral).
            When you use BYOK, you interact directly with those providers under your own agreements with them.
            We are not responsible for the availability, accuracy, or performance of third-party provider services.
            Your use of third-party services through the platform is at your own risk.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Logora shall not be liable for any indirect,
            incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of profits, data, or goodwill,
