            rights, including intellectual property or privacy rights; or (d) content you submit for moderation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">12. Termination</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong>By you:</strong> You may stop using the Service at any time. For paid plans, you may cancel
            your subscription through your account settings; cancellation takes effect at the end of the current
            billing period.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            <strong>By us:</strong> We may suspend or terminate your access to the Service for breach of these Terms,
            with notice where reasonably possible. Upon termination, your right to use the Service ceases immediately.
            We may retain certain data as described in our Privacy Policy or as required by law.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Self-hosted deployments are not affected by cloud service termination;
            you may continue using the open-source software under AGPL v3.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">13. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            The Service is provided &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo; without warranties of any kind,
            either express or implied. We do not warrant that the Service will be uninterrupted, error-free,
            or completely secure. We disclaim all implied warranties, including merchantability, fitness for
            a particular purpose, and non-infringement.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">14. Governing Law and Jurisdiction</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of <strong>France</strong>.
            Any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction
            of the courts of Paris, France. For consumers, this does not affect your statutory rights under
            your local consumer protection laws.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">15. Changes to these Terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">
            We may modify these Terms at any time. Material changes will be communicated via email to active
            Cloud Service users at least 30 days before they take effect. For the self-hosted version,
            the current Terms are always available at this page. Continued use of the Service after changes
            constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">16. Miscellaneous</h2>
          <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
            <li><strong>Severability:</strong> If any provision of these Terms is found unenforceable, the remaining provisions remain in full effect.</li>
            <li><strong>No waiver:</strong> Our failure to enforce any right or provision does not constitute a waiver.</li>
            <li><strong>Assignment:</strong> You may not assign these Terms without our written consent. We may assign these Terms in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets.</li>
            <li><strong>Entire agreement:</strong> These Terms, together with our Privacy Policy and any applicable Data Processing Agreement, constitute the entire agreement between you and Logora regarding the Service.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-surface-900">17. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">For legal inquiries regarding these Terms:</p>
          <div class="mt-3 rounded-lg border border-surface-200 bg-surface-50 p-4">
            <p><strong>Logora</strong></p>
            <p>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@openmoderation.com" class="text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-500">legal@openmoderation.com</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-10 border-surface-200" />

        <p class="text-center">
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-sm font-medium text-brand-600 hover:text-brand-500">
            View our Privacy Policy &rarr;
          </a>
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
